        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I found a bug while using Zend_Date and '0000-00-00 00:00:00' Mysql DateTimes.\n\nHere is a test snippet to reproduce the bug:\n<? \nrequire_once 'Zend\/Date.php';\n$d = new Zend_Date('0000-00-00 00:00:00' ,'YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm:ss');\necho $d->toString('YYYY-MM-dd HH:mm:ss');\n?>\n===========+> \nkiorky@judith ~ $ php  t.php\n00-1-11-30 00:00:00\n\ntz : 'Europe\/Paris'\nphp : PHP 5.2.5-pl0-gentoo (cli) (built: Nov 12 2007 03:04:15)\nOS : Linux  2.6.22-gentoo-r8 \n\n\n\n\n\n"
        },
